{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 13:43:43.798664", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Solution submitted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"dns_server (10.200.0.2)\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"dns_service_down\"]\n\nRecommended next steps (optional):\n- On dns_server: check journalctl -u bind9 -u named for errors, inspect /etc/bind/named.conf and zone files for syntax, then attempt to start the DNS service (systemctl start named or bind9) and verify with ss/netstat that port 53 is listening on 0.0.0.0/10.200.0.2.\n- If service fails to start, capture logs and bind configuration for further diagnosis.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2166, "output_tokens": 145, "total_tokens": 2311, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
